Mitigation.Textual:
Use one of the following SCT delivery methods:
1. use a CA that embeds the SCT within the certificate;
2. embed it within a stapled OCSP response;
3. delivery it using a TLS Extension.

Snippet.Apache:
1. open your Apache configuration file (default: */etc/apache2/sites-available/default-ssl.conf*);
2. add the following lines: ```bash SSLUseStapling on SSLStaplingResponderTimeout 5 SSLStaplingReturnResponderErrors off SSLStaplingCache shmcb:/var/run/ocsp(128000) ```
N.B. restart the server by typing: `sudo service apache2 restart` and make sure that your certificate has been logged (check at [crt.sh](https://crt.sh)).
